Let me take a different tack on the privacy vs transparency 
issue.  I believe that private individuals should have privacy 
and that public institutions and individuals while working in 
the public servant capacity should not.  The latter allows us 
full scrutiny of the State but does not allow the less than 
trustworthy State full scrutiny of us.  They State has to 
justify its level of scrutiny of its individual citizens 
thoroughly.  That they are our "servants" means we do not have 
to justify scrutiny of how they have "served" us.

- samantha


